已经找到解决方法：（I found the solution:）
提供一个metadata-report配置，或者通过注解提供。 （provide a `metadata-report` configuration, or register a config bean to context.）
```
<dubbo:metadata-report address="zookeeper:zkcluster.yourcompany.com?backup=xxx.com
```
就可以很奇妙的创建这个文件了，而且不会报错。。(it's wonderful the file can be created without exception)

生成的文件名：`dubbo-metadata-null-zkcluster.yourcompany.com:9090.cache`，当然这个文件可以创建，只不过`:9090.cache`被截断了，最后这个文件名为`dubbo-metadata-null-zkcluster.yourcompany.com`。后续的代码调用删除，但是实际上不能删除，调用读取，实际上无法读取。

(File will generate as name `dubbo-metadata-null-zkcluster.yourcompany.com:9090.cache`, though this file name is able to create by windows filesytem, the suffix `:9090.cache` is droped, eventually, the filename will be `dubbo-metadata-null-zkcluster.yourcompany.com`. The code logic in AbstractMetadataReport invoke `delete`, but actually won't delete; `read` neighter. )

这里提供一个针对xml配置的 BeanPostProcessor可以修改生成的file路径，将:9090改成_9090：
如果使用 注解形式提供MetadataReportConfig，那就更好了，直接set一些属性注册。

(Here, I provide a BeanPostProcessor that can be used to change meta report cache `file` path, which configured by XML，and change `:9090` to `_9090`. If you register MetadataReportConfig by annotation, it's better and easy, just `setParameters`. )

```
@Component
public class MetaDataReportBeanPostProcessor implements BeanPostProcessor, ApplicationContextAware {

    private ApplicationContext applicationContext;

    @Override
    public void setApplicationContext(ApplicationContext applicationContext) throws BeansException {
        this.applicationContext = applicationContext;
    }

    @Override
    public Object postProcessBeforeInitialization(Object bean, String beanName) throws BeansException {
        return bean;
    }

    @Override
    public Object postProcessAfterInitialization(Object bean, String beanName) throws BeansException {
        if (bean instanceof MetadataReportConfig) {
            String address = ((MetadataReportConfig) bean).getAddress();
            Map<String, String> map = new HashMap<>();
            URL url = UrlUtils.parseURL(address, map);
            String parsedAddress = url.getAddress();
            System.out.println(parsedAddress);

            Map<String, String> parameters = Maps.newHashMap();
            Optional<String> applicationName = Optional.ofNullable(applicationContext.getBean(ApplicationConfig.class)).map(ApplicationConfig::getName);
            String s = System.getProperty("user.home") + "/.dubbo/dubbo-metadata-" + applicationName.orElse("") + "-" + parsedAddress.replaceAll(":", "_") + ".cache";
            parameters.put("file", s);
            ((MetadataReportConfig) bean).setParameters(parameters);
        }
        return bean;
    }
}

```
